{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775880544852,"sessionID":"ses_285458053ffetu4enBlcQXe40Q","part":{"id":"prt_d7aba9ef90011qYByhIVr2YgL4","messageID":"msg_d7aba8fee001eSONmLXIk0EFcx","sessionID":"ses_285458053ffetu4enBlcQXe40Q","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-539f022402b64d75a57d9971283d12be","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-027/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-027/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-027: SDK CodeInterpreterClient\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: 实现 AgentCube Python SDK 中的 `CodeInterpreterClient`，为开发者提供完整的代码解释器会话管理和代码执行功能。该客户端将抽象底层的 HTTP 通信，提供类型安全、易于使用的 API，用于管理代码解释器会话、执行代码、处理文件操作等核心功能。\n6: \n7: ## Purpose\n8: \n9: 为 AgentCube 平台提供完整的 Python SDK 客户端，实现以下目标：\n10: \n11: - 提供简洁、类型安全的 API 用于管理 CodeInterpreter 会话\n12: - 支持同步和异步代码执行模式\n13: - 实现完整的文件操作（上传、下载、写入、列出）\n14: - 提供上下文管理器模式，自动管理会话生命周期\n15: - 集成 Control Plane 和 Data Plane 客户端\n16: - 支持错误处理和重试逻辑\n17: - 提供详细的日志记录和调试支持\n18: \n19: ## Module\n20: \n21: `sdk-python`\n22: \n23: ## Language\n24: \n25: Python 3.10+\n26: \n27: ## Size\n28: \n29: M\n30: \n31: ## Scope\n32: \n33: ### In Scope\n34: \n35: 1. **CodeInterpreterClient 核心功能**\n36:    - 会话创建、检索、删除\n37:    - 代码执行（命令和代码）\n38:    - 文件操作（写入、上传、下载、列出）\n39:    - 上下文管理器支持（`__enter__` / `__exit__`）\n40: \n41: 2. **Control Plane 集成**\n42:    - 通过 Workload Manager 创建会话\n43:    - 会话删除和清理\n44:    - 身份认证和授权\n45: \n46: 3. **Data Plane 集成**\n47:    - 通过 Router 执行命令和代码\n48:    - 文件传输和管理\n49:    - 会话 ID 管理\n50: \n51: 4. **HTTP 客户端**\n52:    - 基于 `requests.Session` 的连接池\n53:    - 超时和重试配置\n54:    - 请求/响应日志\n55: \n56: 5. **异常处理**\n57:    - 自定义异常层次结构\n58:    - 详细的错误信息\n59:    - 命令执行失败处理\n60: \n61: 6. **配置管理**\n62:    - 环境变量解析（`ROUTER_URL`、`WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`）\n63:    - 服务账户令牌加载\n64:    - 可配置的默认值\n65: \n66: ### Out of Scope\n67: \n68: - AgentRuntimeClient 实现（单独的 AR）\n69: - WebSocket 支持\n70: - 会话持久化和恢复\n71: - 高级调试功能\n72: - 自定义执行环境配置\n73: - 分布式会话管理\n74: - 多租户隔离\n75: \n76: ## Impact Analysis\n77: \n78: ### Components Impacted\n79: \n80: 1. **Python SDK 包结构**\n81:    - 新增 `agentcube/code_interpreter.py`\n82:    - 新增 `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py`\n83:    - 新增 `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`\n84:    - 更新 `agentcube/__init__.py` 导出\n85: \n86: 2. **Workload Manager (Control Plane)**\n87:    - 需要支持会话创建和删除 API\n88:    - HTTP 端点：`POST /v1/code-interpreter`、`DELETE /v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{session_id}`\n89: \n90: 3. **Router (Data Plane)**\n91:    - 需要支持命令执行 API\n92:    - 需要支持文件操作 API\n93:    - 需要 `x-agentcube-session-id` 会话头\n94: \n95: 4. **开发者体验**\n96:    - 提供完整的 Python SDK 文档\n97:    - 提供示例代码和教程\n98:    - 支持 pip 安装\n99: \n100: 5. **测试和 CI/CD**\n101:    - 单元测试和集成测试\n102:    - 端到端测试\n103:    - 自动化测试管道\n104: \n105: ### Dependencies\n106: \n107: - `requests ^2.31.0` — HTTP 客户端\n108: - `PyJWT ^2.8.0` — JWT 处理（可选）\n109: - `cryptography ^41.0.0` — 加密支持（可选）\n110: - `pydantic ^2.0.0` — 数据验证（可选，未来增强）\n111: \n112: ### Breaking Changes\n113: \n114: 无破坏性变更。这是全新的 SDK 实现。\n115: \n116: ### Security Considerations\n117: \n118: 1. **认证和授权**\n119:    - 支持 Kubernetes Service Account 令牌\n120:    - 支持自定义认证令牌\n121:    - 令牌安全存储和传输\n122: \n123: 2. **数据传输**\n124:    - 强制 HTTPS（生产环境）\n125:    - 会话 ID 通过安全头部传输\n126:    - 敏感数据加密\n127: \n128: 3. **输入验证**\n129:    - 文件路径验证\n130:    - 命令注入防护\n131:    - 代码执行沙箱\n132: \n133: ## Design Decisions\n134: \n135: ### HTTP 客户端选择\n136: \n137: **选择**: `requests.Session`\n138: \n139: **理由**:\n140: - Python 生态中最成熟和广泛使用的 HTTP 客户端\n141: - 内置连接池和会话管理\n142: - 简单易用的 API\n143: - 良好的文档和社区支持\n144: \n145: ### 会话管理策略\n146: \n147: **选择**: Control Plane 创建会话 + Data Plane 使用会话\n148: \n149: **理由**:\n150: - 分离关注点：会话管理和代码执行\n151: - 支持会话复用\n152: - 符合微服务架构\n153: - 便于扩展和维护\n154: \n155: **实现方式**:\n156: 1. `CodeInterpreterClient` 初始化时创建或复用会话\n157: 2. 通过 `ControlPlaneClient.create_session()` 创建会话\n158: 3. 将 `session_id` 传递给 `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient`\n159: 4. 上下文管理器退出时删除会话\n160: \n161: ### 超时配置策略\n162: \n163: **选择**: 分层超时配置\n164: \n165: **理由**:\n166: - 不同操作需要不同的超时时间\n167: - 支持全局默认和单次覆盖\n168: - 避免长时间挂起\n169: \n170: **配置层次**:\n171: 1. 默认连接超时：5.0 秒\n172: 2. 默认读取超时：120 秒\n173: 3. 代码执行超时可配置\n174: 4. 支持单次调用覆盖\n175: \n176: ### 错误处理策略\n177: \n178: **选择**: 自定义异常层次结构\n179: \n180: **理由**:\n181: - 提供清晰的错误分类\n182: - 便于调用方处理特定错误\n183: - 包含详细的上下文信息\n184: \n185: **异常层次**:\n186: ```\n187: AgentCubeError\n188: ├── SessionError\n189: ├── DataPlaneError\n190: └── CommandExecutionError (包含 exit_code, stderr, command)\n191: ```\n192: \n193: ### 配置解析策略\n194: \n195: **选择**: 参数优先级高于环境变量\n196: \n197: **理由**:\n198: - 提供灵活性\n199: - 支持不同部署场景\n200: - 便于测试和开发\n201: \n202: **优先级**:\n203: 1. 构造函数参数\n204: 2. 环境变量（`ROUTER_URL`、`WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`）\n205: 3. 默认值\n206: \n207: ## Alternatives Considered\n208: \n209: ### Alternative 1: 使用异步 HTTP 客户端\n210: \n211: **描述**: 使用 `httpx` 或 `aiohttp` 实现异步 API\n212: \n213: **优点**:\n214: - 支持异步操作\n215: - 更高的并发性能\n216: - 适合 I/O 密集型场景\n217: \n218: **缺点**:\n219: - 增加学习曲线\n220: - 与现有代码集成复杂\n221: - 调试和维护成本高\n222: \n223: **选择**: 不采纳 - 初始版本使用同步 API，未来可扩展\n224: \n225: ### Alternative 2: 使用 gRPC\n226: \n227: **描述**: 使用 gRPC 协议代替 HTTP REST\n228: \n229: **优点**:\n230: - 更高效的二进制协议\n231: - 强类型接口定义\n232: - 内置流式传输支持\n233: \n234: **缺点**:\n235: - 需要服务器端支持 gRPC\n236: - 增加部署复杂度\n237: - 不易调试\n238: \n239: **选择**: 不采纳 - HTTP REST 更通用，易于集成\n240: \n241: ### Alternative 3: 单一客户端类\n242: \n243: **描述**: 将所有功能合并到一个大客户端类中\n244: \n245: **优点**:\n246: - API 更简单\n247: - 实现更直接\n248: \n249: **缺点**:\n250: - 违反单一职责原则\n251: - 难以测试和维护\n252: - 不便于扩展\n253: \n254: **选择**: 不采纳 - 使用多个专用客户端类\n255: \n256: ### Alternative 4: 使用配置类\n257: \n258: **描述**: 创建专门的 `Configuration` 类管理所有配置\n259: \n260: **优点**:\n261: - 配置集中管理\n262: - 便于传递和验证\n263: \n264: **缺点**:\n265: - 增加代码复杂度\n266: - 不符合 Python 惯例\n267: - 过度设计\n268: \n269: **选择**: 不采纳 - 使用构造函数参数和环境变量\n270: \n271: ## Implementation Plan\n272: \n273: ### Phase 1: 包结构和基础类型 (Day 1-2)\n274: \n275: 1. 创建包目录结构\n276: 2. 定义异常类（`agentcube/exceptions.py`）\n277: 3. 定义工具函数（`agentcube/utils/http.py`、`agentcube/utils/utils.py`、`agentcube/utils/log.py`）\n278: 4. 创建 `pyproject.toml` 配置文件\n279: \n280: ### Phase 2: Control Plane 客户端 (Day 2-3)\n281: \n282: 1. 实现 `ControlPlaneClient` 类\n283: 2. 实现 `create_session()` 方法\n284: 3. 实现 `delete_session()` 方法\n285: 4. 实现 `close()` 方法\n286: 5. 添加单元测试\n287: \n288: ### Phase 3: Data Plane 客户端 (Day 3-4)\n289: \n290: 1. 实现 `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` 类\n291: 2. 实现 `execute_command()` 方法\n292: 3. 实现 `run_code()` 方法\n293: 4. 实现文件操作方法（`write_file`、`upload_file`、`download_file`、`list_files`）\n294: 5. 添加单元测试\n295: \n296: ### Phase 4: CodeInterpreterClient (Day 4-5)\n297: \n298: 1. 实现 `CodeInterpreterClient` 类\n299: 2. 实现构造函数和配置解析\n300: 3. 实现 `_init_data_plane()` 方法\n301: 4. 实现上下文管理器（`__enter__` / `__exit__`）\n302: 5. 实现 `stop()` 方法\n303: 6. 添加单元测试\n304: \n305: ### Phase 5: 集成和端到端测试 (Day 6-7)\n306: \n307: 1. 集成所有客户端\n308: 2. 编写端到端测试\n309: 3. 测试上下文管理器\n310: 4. 测试错误处理\n311: 5. 性能测试\n312: \n313: ### Phase 6: 文档和示例 (Day 7-8)\n314: \n315: 1. 编写 API 文档\n316: 2. 创建使用示例\n317: 3. 编写 README\n318: 4. 准备 pip 发布\n319: \n320: ## Testing Strategy\n321: \n322: ### Unit Tests\n323: \n324: 1. **Control Plane 客户端测试**\n325:    - 会话创建和删除\n326:    - HTTP 请求构造\n327:    - 错误处理\n328:    - 令牌处理\n329: \n330: 2. **Data Plane 客户端测试**\n331:    - 命令执行\n332:    - 代码执行\n333:    - 文件操作\n334:    - 会话头管理\n335: \n336: 3. **CodeInterpreterClient 测试**\n337:    - 上下文管理器\n338:    - 配置解析\n339:    - 错误传播\n340:    - 生命周期管理\n341: \n342: 4. **工具函数测试**\n343:    - HTTP 会话创建\n344:    - 令牌读取\n345:    - 日志配置\n346: \n347: ### Integration Tests\n348: \n349: 1. **Control Plane 集成测试**\n350:    - 与真实 Workload Manager 交互\n351:    - 会话创建和删除流程\n352:    - 认证流程\n353: \n354: 2. **Data Plane 集成测试**\n355:    - 与真实 Router 交互\n356:    - 命令和代码执行\n357:    - 文件传输\n358: \n359: 3. **端到端测试**\n360:    - 完整的使用流程\n361:    - 上下文管理器\n362:    - 错误恢复\n363: \n364: ### Mock Tests\n365: \n366: 1. **HTTP 请求 Mock**\n367:    - 使用 `responses` 或 `pytest-httpx` 模拟 HTTP 请求\n368:    - 测试各种响应场景\n369:    - 测试重试逻辑\n370: \n371: 2. **文件系统 Mock**\n372:    - 模拟文件上传和下载\n373:    - 测试文件路径处理\n374: \n375: ## API Specification\n376: \n377: ### CodeInterpreterClient\n378: \n379: ```python\n380: class CodeInterpreterClient:\n381:     def __init__(\n382:         self,\n383:         name: str = \"my-interpreter\",\n384:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n385:         ttl: int = 3600,\n386:         workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None,\n387:         router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n388:         auth_token: Optional[str] = None,\n389:         verbose: bool = False,\n390:         session_id: Optional[str] = None,\n391:     ) -> None\n392: \n393:     def __enter__(self) -> \"CodeInterpreterClient\"\n394:     def __exit__(self, exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb) -> None\n395:     def stop(self) -> None\n396: \n397:     def execute_command(self, command: str, timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> str\n398:     def run_code(self, language: str, code: str, timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> str\n399:     def write_file(self, content: str, remote_path: str) -> None\n400:     def upload_file(self, local_path: str, remote_path: str) -> None\n401:     def download_file(self, remote_path: str, local_path: str) -> None\n402:     def list_files(self, path: str = \".\") -> Any\n403: ```\n404: \n405: ### HTTP Endpoints (Control Plane)\n406: \n407: - `POST {base_url}/v1/code-interpreter` - 创建会话\n408: - `DELETE {base_url}/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{session_id}` - 删除会话\n409: \n410: ### HTTP Endpoints (Data Plane)\n411: \n412: - `POST {base_url}api/execute` - 执行命令\n413: - `POST {base_url}api/files` - 写入/上传文件\n414: - `GET {base_url}api/files/{path}` - 下载文件\n415: - `GET {base_url}api/files?path={path}` - 列出文件\n416: \n417: ## Configuration\n418: \n419: ### 环境变量\n420: \n421: | 变量 | 描述 | 默认值 |\n422: |------|------|--------|\n423: | `ROUTER_URL` | Router 服务 URL | 必填 |\n424: | `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` | Workload Manager URL | 自动推导 |\n425: | `AUTH_TOKEN` | 认证令牌 | SA 令牌文件 |\n426: \n427: ### 构造函数参数\n428: \n429: | 参数 | 类型 | 默认值 | 描述 |\n430: |------|------|--------|------|\n431: | `name` | str | \"my-interpreter\" | 会话名称 |\n432: | `namespace` | str | \"default\" | 命名空间 |\n433: | `ttl` | int | 3600 | 会话 TTL（秒） |\n434: | `workload_manager_url` | Optional[str] | None | Workload Manager URL |\n435: | `router_url` | Optional[str] | None | Router URL |\n436: | `auth_token` | Optional[str] | None | 认证令牌 |\n437: | `verbose` | bool | False | 详细日志 |\n438: | `session_id` | Optional[str] | None | 现有会话 ID |\n439: \n440: ## Performance Considerations\n441: \n442: 1. **连接池**\n443:    - 使用 `requests.Session` 连接池\n444:    - 默认池大小：10\n445:    - 减少连接建立开销\n446: \n447: 2. **超时配置**\n448:    - 合理的默认超时值\n449:    - 避免长时间挂起\n450:    - 支持单次调用覆盖\n451: \n452: 3. **并发处理**\n453:    - 支持多线程使用\n454:    - 线程安全的 HTTP 客户端\n455:    - 会话隔离\n456: \n457: ## Security Considerations\n458: \n459: 1. **认证**\n460:    - 支持 Service Account 令牌\n461:    - 支持自定义令牌\n462:    - 令牌通过安全头部传输\n463: \n464: 2. **输入验证**\n465:    - 文件路径验证\n466:    - 命令注入防护\n467:    - 参数类型检查\n468: \n469: 3. **日志安全**\n470:    - 不记录敏感信息\n471:    - 令牌脱敏\n472:    - 错误信息脱敏\n473: \n474: ## Monitoring and Metrics\n475: \n476: ### 关键指标\n477: \n478: 1. **客户端指标**\n479:    - 请求数量\n480:    - 请求延迟\n481:    - 错误率\n482:    - 重试次数\n483: \n484: 2. **会话指标**\n485:    - 会话创建数量\n486:    - 会话删除数量\n487:    - 活跃会话数\n488: \n489: 3. **代码执行指标**\n490:    - 代码执行数量\n491:    - 执行成功率\n492:    - 执行延迟\n493: \n494: ### 日志记录\n495: \n496: 1. **请求日志**\n497:    - HTTP 请求和响应\n498:    - 请求 ID\n499:    - 时间戳\n500: \n501: 2. **错误日志**\n502:    - 错误类型\n503:    - 错误消息\n504:    - 堆栈跟踪\n505: \n506: 3. **调试日志**\n507:    - 配置信息\n508:    - 会话 ID\n509:    - 详细操作流程\n510: \n511: ## Open Questions\n512: \n513: 1. **Q1**: 是否需要支持异步 API？\n514:    - **当前**: 仅同步 API\n515:    - **讨论**: 异步 API 可能提供更好的性能\n516:    - **决策**: 初始不支持，未来可扩展\n517: \n518: 2. **Q2**: 是否需要支持会话持久化？\n519:    - **当前**: 会话仅在内存中\n520:    - **讨论**: 持久化可以恢复中断的会话\n521:    - **决策**: 初始不支持，未来可扩展\n522: \n523: 3. **Q3**: 是否需要支持 WebSocket 流式输出？\n524:    - **当前**: 仅同步结果返回\n525:    - **讨论**: 流式输出可以提供更好的用户体验\n526:    - **决策**: 初始不支持，未来可扩展\n527: \n528: ## Success Criteria\n529: \n530: - 单元测试覆盖率 > 80%\n531: - 集成测试全部通过\n532: - API 文档完整且准确\n533: - 示例代码可运行\n534: - 性能满足预期（P99 延迟 < 1s）\n535: - 零安全漏洞\n536: - pip 发布成功\n537: \n538: ## References\n539: \n540: - [Python SDK Design](../../python-sdk/design.md)\n541: - [Python SDK Spec](../../python-sdk/spec.md)\n542: - [Requests Documentation](https://requests.readthedocs.io/)\n543: - [Pydantic Documentation](https://docs.pydantic.dev/)\n544: - [Python Packaging User Guide](https://packaging.python.org/)\n\n(End of file - total 544 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-027: SDK CodeInterpreterClient\n\n## Overview\n\n实现 AgentCube Python SDK 中的 `CodeInterpreterClient`，为开发者提供完整的代码解释器会话管理和代码执行功能。该客户端将抽象底层的 HTTP 通信，提供类型安全、易于使用的 API，用于管理代码解释器会话、执行代码、处理文件操作等核心功能。\n\n## Purpose\n\n为 AgentCube 平台提供完整的 Python SDK 客户端，实现以下目标：\n\n- 提供简洁、类型安全的 API 用于管理 CodeInterpreter 会话\n- 支持同步和异步代码执行模式\n- 实现完整的文件操作（上传、下载、写入、列出）\n- 提供上下文管理器模式，自动管理会话生命周期\n- 集成 Control Plane 和 Data Plane 客户端\n- 支持错误处理和重试逻辑\n- 提供详细的日志记录和调试支持\n\n## Module\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-027/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775880544816,"end":1775880544850}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775880544854,"sessionID":"ses_285458053ffetu4enBlcQXe40Q","part":{"id":"prt_d7aba9ca2001k5W2fV7k18Z59E","messageID":"msg_d7aba8fee001eSONmLXIk0EFcx","sessionID":"ses_285458053ffetu4enBlcQXe40Q","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-5510ad33cc2c42bc9438f836c6434f88","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-028/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-028/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-028: SDK AgentRuntimeClient\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: Implement the `AgentRuntimeClient` in the AgentCube Python SDK, providing a streamlined interface for invoking agent runtime workloads through the Router service. The client abstracts underlying HTTP communication, offering a simple, type-safe API for managing agent runtime sessions and invoking agent workloads with minimal boilerplate.\n6: \n7: ## Purpose\n8: \n9: Provide a Python SDK client for the AgentRuntime service with the following goals:\n10: \n11: - Simple, intuitive API for invoking agent runtime workloads\n12: - Automatic session ID bootstrap and management\n13: - Context manager support for automatic resource cleanup\n14: - Integrated Data Plane communication via Router\n15: - Proper error handling and timeout configuration\n16: - Detailed logging and debugging support\n17: \n18: ## Module\n19: \n20: `sdk-python`\n21: \n22: ## Language\n23: \n24: Python 3.10+\n25: \n26: ## Size\n27: \n28: M\n29: \n30: ## Scope\n31: \n32: ### In Scope\n33: \n34: 1. **AgentRuntimeClient Core Functionality**\n35:    - Session ID bootstrap from Router\n36:    - Agent workload invocation\n37:    - Context manager support (`__enter__` / `__exit__`)\n38:    - Resource cleanup\n39: \n40: 2. **Data Plane Integration**\n41:    - HTTP communication via Router\n42:    - Session header management (`x-agentcube-session-id`)\n43:    - Timeout configuration\n44:    - Connection pooling\n45: \n46: 3. **Configuration Management**\n47:    - Environment variable resolution (`ROUTER_URL`)\n48:    - Configurable timeouts (read, connect)\n49:    - Session ID reuse support\n50: \n51: 4. **Error Handling**\n52:    - Session validation\n53:    - HTTP error propagation\n54:    - Clear error messages\n55: \n56: ### Out of Scope\n57: \n58: - Agent lifecycle management (create, delete, list)\n59: - Session persistence and recovery\n60: - Streaming responses\n61: - Webhook support\n62: - Metrics and observability\n63: - Async API (can be added in future AR)\n64: - Custom retry logic\n65: \n66: ## Impact Analysis\n67: \n68: ### Components Impacted\n69: \n70: 1. **Python SDK Package Structure**\n71:    - New file: `agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n72:    - New file: `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n73:    - Update `agentcube/__init__.py` exports\n74: \n75: 2. **Router Service (Data Plane)**\n76:    - GET `{router}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/` - Bootstrap session ID\n77:    - POST `{router}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/` - Invoke agent\n78: \n79: 3. **Developer Experience**\n80:    - Provide Python SDK documentation\n81:    - Example code for agent invocation\n82:    - pip package distribution\n83: \n84: 4. **Testing and CI/CD**\n85:    - Unit tests for client classes\n86:    - Integration tests with Router\n87:    - E2E testing\n88: \n89: ### Dependencies\n90: \n91: - `requests ^2.31.0` - HTTP client\n92: \n93: ### Breaking Changes\n94: \n95: None. This is a new SDK feature.\n96: \n97: ### Security Considerations\n98: \n99: 1. **Authentication**\n100:    - Router handles JWT validation\n101:    - Session ID transmitted via headers\n102:    - No auth token directly set by SDK\n103: \n104: 2. **Data Transmission**\n105:    - HTTPS recommended (production)\n106:    - Session ID via `x-agentcube-session-id` header\n107:    - Payloads as JSON\n108: \n109: 3. **Input Validation**\n110:    - Session ID validation before invoke\n111:    - Type checking via Python type hints\n112: \n113: ## Design Decisions\n114: \n115: ### HTTP Client Selection\n116: \n117: **Choice**: `requests.Session`\n118: \n119: **Rationale**:\n120: - Mature and widely-used HTTP client\n121: - Built-in connection pooling\n122: - Simple, intuitive API\n123: - Good documentation and community support\n124: \n125: ### Session Management Strategy\n126: \n127: **Choice**: Bootstrap session ID via GET request\n128: \n129: **Rationale**:\n130: - Router manages session lifecycle\n131: - No Control Plane involvement needed\n132: - Simple and stateless\n133: - Supports session reuse\n134: \n135: **Implementation**:\n136: 1. `AgentRuntimeClient` initializes `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`\n137: 2. If `session_id` not provided, call `bootstrap_session_id()`\n138: 3. GET on invocation URL returns `x-agentcube-session-id` header\n139: 4. POST requests use the session ID header\n140: \n141: ### Timeout Configuration Strategy\n142: \n143: **Choice**: Configurable defaults with per-call override\n144: \n145: **Rationale**:\n146: - Different workloads have different timeout needs\n147: - Support global defaults\n148: - Allow per-invocation override\n149: \n150: **Configuration**:\n151: 1. Default connect timeout: 5.0 seconds\n152: 2. Default read timeout: 120 seconds\n153: 3. Invoke method accepts optional `timeout` parameter\n154: 4. Timeout tuple: `(connect_timeout, read_timeout)`\n155: \n156: ### Error Handling Strategy\n157: \n158: **Choice**: Standard exceptions with clear messages\n159: \n160: **Rationale**:\n161: - Python's exception hierarchy is sufficient\n162: - `requests` provides detailed HTTP errors\n163: - Custom `ValueError` for missing session ID\n164: - Simpler than custom exception hierarchy\n165: \n166: ### Configuration Resolution Strategy\n167: \n168: **Choice**: Parameter priority over environment variables\n169: \n170: **Rationale**:\n171: - Provide flexibility\n172: - Support different deployment scenarios\n173: - Ease of testing\n174: \n175: **Priority**:\n176: 1. Constructor parameters\n177: 2. Environment variable (`ROUTER_URL`)\n178: 3. Default values\n179: \n180: ## Alternatives Considered\n181: \n182: ### Alternative 1: Async HTTP Client\n183: \n184: **Description**: Use `httpx` or `aiohttp` for async API\n185: \n186: **Pros**:\n187: - Supports async operations\n188: - Better concurrency for I/O-bound tasks\n189: \n190: **Cons**:\n191: - Steeper learning curve\n192: - More complex integration\n193: - Not needed for initial use cases\n194: \n195: **Decision**: Rejected - Sync API sufficient for v1, can extend later\n196: \n197: ### Alternative 2: gRPC Protocol\n198: \n199: **Description**: Use gRPC instead of HTTP REST\n200: \n201: **Pros**:\n202: - Efficient binary protocol\n203: - Strong typing\n204: - Built-in streaming support\n205: \n206: **Cons**:\n207: - Requires server-side gRPC support\n208: - More complex deployment\n209: - Harder to debug\n210: \n211: **Decision**: Rejected - HTTP REST is more universal and easier to integrate\n212: \n213: ### Alternative 3: Single Client Class\n214: \n215: **Description**: Merge Data Plane into main client\n216: \n217: **Pros**:\n218: - Simpler API\n219: - Fewer files\n220: \n221: **Cons**:\n222: - Violates single responsibility principle\n223: - Harder to test\n224: - Less flexible\n225: \n226: **Decision**: Rejected - Separate Data Plane client is cleaner\n227: \n228: ### Alternative 4: Control Plane Session Management\n229: \n230: **Description**: Use Control Plane for session creation\n231: \n232: **Pros**:\n233: - Consistent with CodeInterpreterClient\n234: \n235: **Cons**:\n236: - Unnecessary complexity\n237: - Router already handles sessions\n238: - Extra dependencies\n239: \n240: **Decision**: Rejected - Router-only approach is simpler\n241: \n242: ## Implementation Plan\n243: \n244: ### Phase 1: Data Plane Client (Day 1)\n245: \n246: 1. Implement `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` class\n247: 2. Implement `bootstrap_session_id()` method\n248: 3. Implement `invoke()` method\n249: 4. Implement `close()` method\n250: 5. Add unit tests\n251: \n252: ### Phase 2: Agent Runtime Client (Day 1-2)\n253: \n254: 1. Implement `AgentRuntimeClient` class\n255: 2. Implement constructor and configuration resolution\n256: 3. Implement context manager (`__enter__` / `__exit__`)\n257: 4. Implement `invoke()` method\n258: 5. Implement `close()` method\n259: 6. Add unit tests\n260: \n261: ### Phase 3: Integration and Testing (Day 2)\n262: \n263: 1. Update `agentcube/__init__.py` exports\n264: 2. Integration tests with Router\n265: 3. E2E testing\n266: 4. Error scenario testing\n267: \n268: ### Phase 4: Documentation (Day 2-3)\n269: \n270: 1. Write API documentation\n271: 2. Create usage examples\n272: 3. Update README\n273: \n274: ## Testing Strategy\n275: \n276: ### Unit Tests\n277: \n278: 1. **AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient Tests**\n279:    - Session ID bootstrap\n280:    - Invoke request construction\n281:    - Session header management\n282:    - Timeout handling\n283:    - Error propagation\n284: \n285: 2. **AgentRuntimeClient Tests**\n286:    - Configuration resolution\n287:    - Session ID initialization\n288:    - Context manager behavior\n289:    - Invoke delegation\n290:    - Cleanup\n291: \n292: ### Integration Tests\n293: \n294: 1. **Router Integration Tests**\n295:    - Bootstrap session ID from real Router\n296:    - Invoke with real payload\n297:    - Session header validation\n298:    - Timeout scenarios\n299: \n300: 2. **E2E Tests**\n301:    - Complete usage flow\n302:    - Context manager lifecycle\n303:    - Error recovery\n304: \n305: ### Mock Tests\n306: \n307: 1. **HTTP Request Mock**\n308:    - Use `responses` or similar to mock HTTP\n309:    - Test various response scenarios\n310:    - Test error conditions\n311: \n312: ## API Specification\n313: \n314: ### AgentRuntimeClient\n315: \n316: ```python\n317: class AgentRuntimeClient:\n318:     def __init__(\n319:         self,\n320:         agent_name: str,\n321:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n322:         router_url: str | None = None,\n323:         verbose: bool = False,\n324:         session_id: str | None = None,\n325:         timeout: int = 120,\n326:         connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n327:     ) -> None\n328: \n329:     def __enter__(self) -> \"AgentRuntimeClient\"\n330:     def __exit__(self, exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb) -> None\n331: \n332:     def invoke(self, payload: dict[str, object], timeout: float | None = None) -> dict[str, object]\n333: \n334:     def close(self) -> None\n335: ```\n336: \n337: ### AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n338: \n339: ```python\n340: class AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient:\n341:     SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"\n342: \n343:     def __init__(\n344:         self,\n345:         router_url: str,\n346:         namespace: str,\n347:         agent_name: str,\n348:         timeout: int = 120,\n349:         connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n350:         pool_connections: int = 10,\n351:         pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n352:     ) -> None\n353: \n354:     def bootstrap_session_id(self) -> str\n355: \n356:     def invoke(self, session_id: str, payload: dict[str, Any], timeout: float | None = None) -> requests.Response\n357: \n358:     def close(self) -> None\n359: ```\n360: \n361: ### HTTP Endpoints\n362: \n363: - `GET {router}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/` - Bootstrap session ID\n364:   - Returns: `x-agentcube-session-id` header\n365: \n366: - `POST {router}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/` - Invoke agent\n367:   - Headers: `x-agentcube-session-id`, `Content-Type: application/json`\n368:   - Body: JSON payload\n369: \n370: ## Configuration\n371: \n372: ### Environment Variables\n373: \n374: | Variable | Description | Default |\n375: |----------|-------------|---------|\n376: | `ROUTER_URL` | Router service URL | Required |\n377: \n378: ### Constructor Parameters\n379: \n380: | Parameter | Type | Default | Description |\n381: |-----------|------|---------|-------------|\n382: | `agent_name` | str | Required | Agent runtime name |\n383: | `namespace` | str | \"default\" | Kubernetes namespace |\n384: | `router_url` | str \\| None | None | Router URL |\n385: | `verbose` | bool | False | Enable verbose logging |\n386: | `session_id` | str \\| None | None | Existing session ID to reuse |\n387: | `timeout` | int | 120 | Read timeout in seconds |\n388: | `connect_timeout` | float | 5.0 | Connect timeout in seconds |\n389: \n390: ## Performance Considerations\n391: \n392: 1. **Connection Pooling**\n393:    - `requests.Session` with `HTTPAdapter`\n394:    - Default pool size: 10\n395:    - Reduces connection overhead\n396: \n397: 2. **Timeout Configuration**\n398:    - Reasonable defaults\n399:    - Prevents indefinite hangs\n400:    - Per-call override support\n401: \n402: 3. **Session Reuse**\n403:    - Existing `session_id` can be passed\n404:    - Avoids extra GET request\n405:    - Multiple invocations share session\n406: \n407: ## Security Considerations\n408: \n409: 1. **Session Management**\n410:    - Router handles session validation\n411:    - Session ID transmitted via headers\n412:    - No auth token directly managed\n413: \n414: 2. **Input Validation**\n415:    - Session ID checked before invoke\n416:    - Type hints for API contracts\n417:    - Payloads must be JSON-serializable\n418: \n419: 3. **Logging Security**\n420:    - No sensitive data in logs\n421:    - Session ID may be logged (consider filtering)\n422: \n423: ## Monitoring and Metrics\n424: \n425: ### Key Metrics\n426: \n427: 1. **Client Metrics**\n428:    - Request count\n429:    - Request latency\n430:    - Error rate\n431: \n432: 2. **Session Metrics**\n433:    - Session bootstrap count\n434:    - Session reuse count\n435: \n436: 3. **Invocation Metrics**\n437:    - Invocation count\n438:    - Success rate\n439:    - Invocation latency\n440: \n441: ### Logging\n442: \n443: 1. **Request Logs**\n444:    - HTTP requests/responses\n445:    - Session IDs\n446:    - Timestamps\n447: \n448: 2. **Error Logs**\n449:    - Error types\n450:    - Error messages\n451:    - Stack traces\n452: \n453: 3. **Debug Logs**\n454:    - Configuration details\n455:    - Session bootstrap\n456:    - Request details\n457: \n458: ## Open Questions\n459: \n460: 1. **Q1**: Should we implement retry logic for transient failures?\n461:    - **Current**: No retry logic\n462:    - **Discussion**: Could improve reliability\n463:    - **Decision**: Not in v1, can be added later\n464: \n465: 2. **Q2**: Should we support async API?\n466:    - **Current**: Sync-only\n467:    - **Discussion**: Async may improve performance for concurrent invocations\n468:    - **Decision**: Not in v1, can be added later\n469: \n470: 3. **Q3**: Should we expose metrics?\n471:    - **Current**: No metrics collection\n472:    - **Discussion**: Would help with observability\n473:    - **Decision**: Not in v1, can be added later\n474: \n475: ## Success Criteria\n476: \n477: - Unit tests pass with >80% coverage\n478: - Integration tests pass with real Router\n479: - API documentation complete and accurate\n480: - Example code works end-to-end\n481: - Performance meets requirements (P99 latency < 200ms)\n482: - Zero security vulnerabilities\n483: - Package publishes successfully to PyPI\n484: \n485: ## References\n486: \n487: - [Python SDK Design](../../python-sdk/design.md)\n488: - [Python SDK Spec](../../python-sdk/spec.md)\n489: - [Requests Documentation](https://requests.readthedocs.io/)\n\n(End of file - total 489 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-028: SDK AgentRuntimeClient\n\n## Overview\n\nImplement the `AgentRuntimeClient` in the AgentCube Python SDK, providing a streamlined interface for invoking agent runtime workloads through the Router service. The client abstracts underlying HTTP communication, offering a simple, type-safe API for managing agent runtime sessions and invoking agent workloads with minimal boilerplate.\n\n## Purpose\n\nProvide a Python SDK client for the AgentRuntime service with the following goals:\n\n- Simple, intuitive API for invoking agent runtime workloads\n- Automatic session ID bootstrap and management\n- Context manager support for automatic resource cleanup\n- Integrated Data Plane communication via Router\n- Proper error handling and timeout configuration\n- Detailed logging and debugging support\n\n## Module\n\n`sdk-python`","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-028/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775880544813,"end":1775880544852}}}}
