{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775880581161,"sessionID":"ses_285458053ffetu4enBlcQXe40Q","part":{"id":"prt_d7abb2d8c001jqzCMOSWNKqWym","messageID":"msg_d7abb159c001OMrBsIsHAmBa7x","sessionID":"ses_285458053ffetu4enBlcQXe40Q","type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"toolu_tool-e72b6f6c652741e68dd535003a7e890e","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"ls -la /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/config/","description":"List config directory contents"},"output":"total 16\ndrwxr-xr-x  4 root root 4096 Apr 11 00:47 .\ndrwxr-xr-x 23 root root 4096 Apr 11 12:04 ..\ndrwxr-xr-x  3 root root 4096 Apr 11 00:39 crd\ndrwxr-xr-x  2 root root 4096 Apr 11 00:47 samples\n","metadata":{"output":"total 16\ndrwxr-xr-x  4 root root 4096 Apr 11 00:47 .\ndrwxr-xr-x 23 root root 4096 Apr 11 12:04 ..\ndrwxr-xr-x  3 root root 4096 Apr 11 00:39 crd\ndrwxr-xr-x  2 root root 4096 Apr 11 00:47 samples\n","exit":0,"description":"List config directory contents","truncated":false},"title":"List config directory contents","time":{"start":1775880581139,"end":1775880581160}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775880581174,"sessionID":"ses_285458053ffetu4enBlcQXe40Q","part":{"id":"prt_d7abb2ff5001aj9YfOJqnOvZIi","messageID":"msg_d7abb159c001OMrBsIsHAmBa7x","sessionID":"ses_285458053ffetu4enBlcQXe40Q","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-069040c21e8a422fa64c71274e604ead","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/README.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/README.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AgentCube Python SDK\n2: \n3: Python client library (`agentcube-sdk`) for creating Code Interpreter sessions via the Workload Manager (control plane) and executing code/files via the Router (data plane), plus invoking AgentRuntime workloads through the Router.\n4: \n5: ## Features\n6: \n7: - **Code Interpreter**: Create sessions, execute commands, run Python code, manage files\n8: - **Agent Runtime**: Bootstrap sessions, invoke agents with custom payloads\n9: - **HTTP Clients**: Connection pooling, configurable timeouts, automatic retries\n10: - **Authentication**: Support for Bearer tokens and Kubernetes service account tokens\n11: - **Context Managers**: Automatic session cleanup with `with` statements\n12: \n13: ## Installation\n14: \n15: ```bash\n16: pip install agentcube-sdk\n17: ```\n18: \n19: ## Quick Start\n20: \n21: ### Code Interpreter\n22: \n23: ```python\n24: from agentcube import CodeInterpreterClient\n25: \n26: # Create a new session\n27: client = CodeInterpreterClient(\n28:     name=\"my-interpreter\",\n29:     namespace=\"default\",\n30:     router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n31:     workload_manager_url=\"http://workload-manager:8080\",\n32: )\n33: \n34: # Execute a command\n35: output = client.execute_command(\"ls -la\")\n36: print(output)\n37: \n38: # Run Python code\n39: result = client.run_code(\"python\", \"print('Hello, World!')\")\n40: print(result)\n41: \n42: # Write a file\n43: client.write_file(\"Hello, World!\", \"/tmp/hello.txt\")\n44: \n45: # Upload a file\n46: client.upload_file(\"./local.txt\", \"/tmp/remote.txt\")\n47: \n48: # Download a file\n49: client.download_file(\"/tmp/remote.txt\", \"./downloaded.txt\")\n50: \n51: # List files\n52: files = client.list_files(\"/tmp\")\n53: print(files)\n54: \n55: # Clean up\n56: client.stop()\n57: ```\n58: \n59: ### Using Context Manager\n60: \n61: ```python\n62: from agentcube import CodeInterpreterClient\n63: \n64: with CodeInterpreterClient(\n65:     name=\"my-interpreter\",\n66:     namespace=\"default\",\n67:     router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n68: ) as client:\n69:     output = client.execute_command(\"ls -la\")\n70:     print(output)\n71: # Session is automatically cleaned up\n72: ```\n73: \n74: ### Agent Runtime\n75: \n76: ```python\n77: from agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient\n78: \n79: # Create a client (session is automatically bootstrapped)\n80: client = AgentRuntimeClient(\n81:     agent_name=\"my-agent\",\n82:     namespace=\"default\",\n83:     router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n84: )\n85: \n86: # Invoke the agent\n87: response = client.invoke({\n88:     \"input\": \"Hello, Agent!\",\n89:     \"context\": {\"user\": \"alice\"}\n90: })\n91: print(response)\n92: \n93: # Clean up\n94: client.close()\n95: ```\n96: \n97: ### Using Context Manager\n98: \n99: ```python\n100: from agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient\n101: \n102: with AgentRuntimeClient(\n103:     agent_name=\"my-agent\",\n104:     namespace=\"default\",\n105:     router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n106: ) as client:\n107:     response = client.invoke({\"input\": \"Hello, Agent!\"})\n108:     print(response)\n109: # Session is automatically cleaned up\n110: ```\n111: \n112: ## Configuration\n113: \n114: ### Environment Variables\n115: \n116: - `ROUTER_URL`: Default Router URL (can be overridden in constructor)\n117: - `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`: Default Workload Manager URL (for Code Interpreter control plane)\n118: \n119: ### Authentication\n120: \n121: The SDK supports Bearer token authentication:\n122: \n123: ```python\n124: # Direct token\n125: client = CodeInterpreterClient(\n126:     router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n127:     auth_token=\"my-token\"\n128: )\n129: \n130: # Kubernetes service account token (automatic)\n131: client = CodeInterpreterClient(\n132:     router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n133:     # Token is automatically read from /var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token\n134: )\n135: ```\n136: \n137: ### Timeouts\n138: \n139: Default timeouts:\n140: - Connect timeout: 5.0 seconds\n141: - Read timeout: 120 seconds\n142: \n143: Custom timeouts:\n144: \n145: ```python\n146: from agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient\n147: \n148: client = AgentRuntimeClient(\n149:     agent_name=\"my-agent\",\n150:     router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n151:     timeout=60,           # Read timeout in seconds\n152:     connect_timeout=2.0,  # Connect timeout in seconds\n153: )\n154: ```\n155: \n156: Per-call timeout override:\n157: \n158: ```python\n159: # Code Interpreter\n160: output = client.execute_command(\"sleep 10\", timeout=30.0)\n161: \n162: # Agent Runtime\n163: response = client.invoke({\"input\": \"test\"}, timeout=60.0)\n164: ```\n165: \n166: ## Error Handling\n167: \n168: ```python\n169: from agentcube import CodeInterpreterClient\n170: from agentcube.exceptions import CommandExecutionError\n171: \n172: try:\n173:     client = CodeInterpreterClient(router_url=\"http://router:8080\")\n174:     output = client.execute_command(\"ls /invalid\")\n175: except CommandExecutionError as e:\n176:     print(f\"Command failed with exit code {e.exit_code}\")\n177:     print(f\"Error: {e.stderr}\")\n178: except ValueError as e:\n179:     print(f\"Configuration error: {e}\")\n180: ```\n181: \n182: ## API Reference\n183: \n184: ### CodeInterpreterClient\n185: \n186: | Method | Description |\n187: |--------|-------------|\n188: | `execute_command(command, timeout)` | Execute a shell command |\n189: | `run_code(language, code, timeout)` | Run code in a specific language |\n190: | `write_file(content, remote_path)` | Write content to a remote file |\n191: | `upload_file(local_path, remote_path)` | Upload a local file |\n192: | `download_file(remote_path, local_path)` | Download a remote file |\n193: | `list_files(path)` | List files in a directory |\n194: | `stop()` | Stop the session and cleanup |\n195: \n196: ### AgentRuntimeClient\n197: \n198: | Method | Description |\n199: |--------|-------------|\n200: | `invoke(payload, timeout)` | Invoke the agent with a payload |\n201: | `close()` | Close the HTTP session |\n202: \n203: ## Development\n204: \n205: ### Running Tests\n206: \n207: ```bash\n208: pytest tests/ -v\n209: ```\n210: \n211: ### Code Style\n212: \n213: ```bash\n214: ruff check agentcube/\n215: ruff format agentcube/\n216: ```\n217: \n218: ### Type Checking\n219: \n220: ```bash\n221: mypy agentcube/\n222: ```\n223: \n224: ## License\n225: \n226: [Specify your license here]\n\n(End of file - total 226 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AgentCube Python SDK\n\nPython client library (`agentcube-sdk`) for creating Code Interpreter sessions via the Workload Manager (control plane) and executing code/files via the Router (data plane), plus invoking AgentRuntime workloads through the Router.\n\n## Features\n\n- **Code Interpreter**: Create sessions, execute commands, run Python code, manage files\n- **Agent Runtime**: Bootstrap sessions, invoke agents with custom payloads\n- **HTTP Clients**: Connection pooling, configurable timeouts, automatic retries\n- **Authentication**: Support for Bearer tokens and Kubernetes service account tokens\n- **Context Managers**: Automatic session cleanup with `with` statements\n\n## Installation\n\n```bash\npip install agentcube-sdk\n```\n\n## Quick Start\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/README.md","time":{"start":1775880581142,"end":1775880581172}}}}
