{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775880585148,"sessionID":"ses_285458053ffetu4enBlcQXe40Q","part":{"id":"prt_d7abb3f89001YiwRbLBknGQL7M","messageID":"msg_d7abb30640019oWPtgNr02bTh2","sessionID":"ses_285458053ffetu4enBlcQXe40Q","type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"toolu_tool-9b696d9d490740708fc73a0c4039cf56","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"find /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z -name \"*.yaml\" | xargs grep -l \"kind: Deployment\\|kind: Service\\|kind: ConfigMap\" 2>/dev/null | head -5","description":"Find existing resource definitions"},"output":"","metadata":{"output":"","exit":0,"description":"Find existing resource definitions","truncated":false},"title":"Find existing resource definitions","time":{"start":1775880585127,"end":1775880585146}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775880585152,"sessionID":"ses_285458053ffetu4enBlcQXe40Q","part":{"id":"prt_d7abb3b06001kNo9jKQtXzoe39","messageID":"msg_d7abb30640019oWPtgNr02bTh2","sessionID":"ses_285458053ffetu4enBlcQXe40Q","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-a1fdb0a32acc4befb3b5a5d0aead5dcb","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/design.md","limit":100},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-020: CLI pack 命令 — Design\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: The `pack` command in the AgentCube CLI is responsible for validating and preparing an agent workspace, merging CLI overrides into metadata, optionally generating a `Dockerfile`, and reporting paths to the packaged artifacts.\n6: \n7: **Module:** `cmd/cli`  \n8: **Language:** Python  \n9: **Source Root:** `/tmp/agentcube-ref/cmd/cli/`\n10: \n11: ## Architecture\n12: \n13: ### Components\n14: \n15: | Component | Location | Responsibility |\n16: |-----------|----------|----------------|\n17: | `PackRuntime` | `agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py` | Core packing logic implementation |\n18: | `MetadataService` | `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | Metadata loading, saving, and validation |\n19: | `MetadataOptions` | `agentcube/models/pack_models.py` | Dataclass for CLI option parsing |\n20: | `pack` command | `agentcube/cli/main.py` | Typer command definition and CLI entry point |\n21: \n22: ### Data Flow\n23: \n24: ```\n25: CLI Options → MetadataOptions → PackRuntime.pack()\n26:                                       ↓\n27:                      _validate_workspace_structure()\n28:                                       ↓\n29:                       _load_or_create_metadata()\n30:                                       ↓\n31:                       _apply_option_overrides()\n32:                                       ↓\n33:                     _validate_language_compatibility()\n34:                                       ↓\n35:                          _process_dependencies()\n36:                                       ↓\n37:                          _generate_dockerfile()\n38:                                       ↓\n39:                      _update_pack_metadata()\n40:                                       ↓\n41:                          _prepare_output_path()\n42:                                       ↓\n43:                             Return result\n44: ```\n45: \n46: ## Detailed Implementation\n47: \n48: ### 1. CLI Command (`agentcube/cli/main.py`)\n49: \n50: ```python\n51: def pack(\n52:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True),\n53:     agent_name: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--agent-name\", help=\"Override the agent name\"),\n54:     language: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--language\", help=\"Programming language (python, java)\"),\n55:     entrypoint: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--entrypoint\", help=\"Override the entrypoint command\"),\n56:     port: Optional[int] = typer.Option(None, \"--port\", help=\"Port to expose in the Dockerfile\"),\n57:     build_mode: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--build-mode\", help=\"Build strategy: local or cloud\"),\n58:     description: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--description\", help=\"Agent description\"),\n59:     output: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--output\", help=\"Output path for packaged workspace\"),\n60:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n61: ) -> None:\n62:     \"\"\"Package an agent workspace by validating structure and generating metadata.\"\"\"\n63: ```\n64: \n65: **Command behavior:**\n66: - Resolves workspace path relative to current directory if not absolute\n67: - Creates `PackRuntime` instance with verbose flag\n68: - Collects options into a dictionary\n69: - Calls `PackRuntime.pack(workspace_path, **options)`\n70: - Handles exceptions via `_handle_error(e, \"pack\", verbose)`\n71: \n72: ### 2. PackRuntime (`agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py`)\n73: \n74: #### Class Structure\n75: \n76: ```python\n77: class PackRuntime:\n78:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None:\n79:         self.verbose = verbose\n80:         self.logger = get_logger(__name__, level=logging.DEBUG if verbose else logging.INFO)\n81: ```\n82: \n83: #### Main Method: `pack()`\n84: \n85: ```python\n86: def pack(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n87:     \"\"\"Package an agent workspace.\n88: \n89:     Returns:\n90:         Dict containing:\n91:         - agent_name: str\n92:         - workspace_path: str (absolute path)\n93:         - metadata_path: str\n94:         - dockerfile_path: Optional[str]\n95:         - language: str\n96:         - entrypoint: str\n97:         - port: int\n98:     \"\"\"\n99:     with Progress() as progress:\n100:         task = progress.add_task(\"[cyan]Packing workspace...\", total=100)\n\n(Showing lines 1-100 of 460. Use offset=101 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-020: CLI pack 命令 — Design\n\n## Overview\n\nThe `pack` command in the AgentCube CLI is responsible for validating and preparing an agent workspace, merging CLI overrides into metadata, optionally generating a `Dockerfile`, and reporting paths to the packaged artifacts.\n\n**Module:** `cmd/cli`  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Source Root:** `/tmp/agentcube-ref/cmd/cli/`\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Components\n\n| Component | Location | Responsibility |\n|-----------|----------|----------------|\n| `PackRuntime` | `agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py` | Core packing logic implementation |\n| `MetadataService` | `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | Metadata loading, saving, and validation |\n| `MetadataOptions` | `agentcube/models/pack_models.py` | Dataclass for CLI option parsing |\n| `pack` command | `agentcube/cli/main.py` | Typer command definition and CLI entry point |","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/design.md","time":{"start":1775880585121,"end":1775880585150}}}}
